Right i just figured out after all this time the most obvious thing EVER!

in the code:
[code]			characterfile.write("fightMode = ", 0, 12);
			characterfile.write(Integer.toString(p.fightMode), 0, Integer.toString(p.fightMode).length());
			characterfile.newLine();[/code]


the "12" means how long it is including the spaces and "EQUALS" sign.

so in my part:
[code]			characterfile.write("inPriz = ", 0, #);
			characterfile.write(Integer.toString(p.inPriz), 0, Integer.toString(p.inPriz).length());
			characterfile.newLine();[/code]

Where the "#" is there should be the number "9"

